Tripoli, March 22, 2022 (Reuters/NAN) Libya will on Tuesday resume domestic air travel weeks  after country’s political crisis closed airspace. Global Air scheduled a Tripoli-Benghazi flight for Tuesday afternoon, signalling resumption of domestic air travel. The United Nations had urged the reopening of Libya’s skies in line with a 2020 ceasefire between the main warring factions to allow unhindered travel within the country.